        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30994",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Fabien:\nTake a look at Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter->_getTmpDir().\nIt has a very good detection and is captable of detecting the tmp path even if no ENV or SERVER is set.\n\nAdditionally it checks if the tmp dir is writable and when not, it throws an exception, which is better there than above in Zend_Cache.. for example \"No cache_dir given, temporary directory not writeable\"\n\nI would propose that you add this method also in your class.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-15T01:38:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-15T01:38:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31061",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "just commited something better into SVN trunk\n\ncan you try it ?\n\n(you have only to take the Backend.php file from SVN trunk)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-16T01:56:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-16T01:56:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31062",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'll be able to try it coming Monday (18th). I'll let you know if your fix did the trick. Do you have a revision number for me? Or is it just in trunk?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-16T02:09:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-16T02:09:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31099",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just tried it. It makes no difference. I'm still getting the same exception with the \"cache_dir must be a directory\" error.\n\nThere's no problem in figuring out the temp directory. That goes well, but _isGoodTmpDir()'s attempt with is_writable() seems to fail silently. It just seems to pass the test.\n\nIn my personal opinion, caching should always be *optional*. Currently ZF expects the user always wants to cache data, and personally I believe that decision is up to the user. Not the software.\n\nThe current routine to check for the temp directory looks fine to me, but I don't think any ZF component should use auto-cache at all.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-18T05:53:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-18T05:53:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31100",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Forgot to add this to my previous comment. As currently stated in the Zend_Locale documentation caching is still optional. No migration notes were added either.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-18T06:00:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-18T06:00:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31197",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "so it's not a Zend_Cache issue but a Zend_Locale one\n\nI remove Zend_Cache as affected component\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fab",
                        "name": "fab",
                        "displayName": "Fabien MARTY",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-20T13:12:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-20T13:12:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31198",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aballard",
                        "name": "aballard",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Ballard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That is what I am seeing as well. Since upgrading to 1.8.0 Zend_Validate_Int is choking on the 'cache_dir must be a directory' exception. Apparently the validator is trying to pull Zend_Locale_Data from Zend_Cache. So instead of the site either being unable to pull the data from cache or simply using default error text without the locale, the site just blows up. I could catch the exception in my code and ignore it, but that won't make the validator function.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=aballard",
                        "name": "aballard",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Ballard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-20T13:30:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-20T13:30:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31304",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There are 2 solutions:\n\n* Use a cache with write permissions\nor\n* Disable the cache usage within Zend_Locale\n\nSecond is depreciated but possible as it results in a massive performance decreasement.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-24T03:11:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-24T03:11:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31307",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I vote for the latter. As described in the documentation, caching with Zend_Locale should be optional and should be up to the user to decide if he\/she is going to use it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-24T11:53:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-24T11:53:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31308",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you point me to the chapter where you read that cache is not set ?\n\nThe actual documentation reads:\n{quote}\nWhen no cache is set, then <classname>Zend_Locale<\/classname> will automatically set a cache itself. Sometimes it is wished to prevent that a cache is set, even if this degrades performance. In this case the static <methodname>disableCache(true)<\/methodname> method should be used. It does not only disable the actual set cache, without erasing it, but also prevents that a cache is automatically generated when no cache is set.\n{quote}\n\nSo I don't get the reason why you \"vote for the latter\"...using the option seems the better way for me than voting :-)\n\nPS: But this has nothing to do with the problem that the tempoary path of PHP is not detected.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-24T12:31:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-24T12:38:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31309",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.locale.html#zend.locale.cache\n\nIt clearly says \"*can be* speed up\" :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-24T12:37:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-24T12:37:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31310",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Using a false cache will also decrease performance or negotate it completly... but I don't think that this should be mentioned into this chapter. Anyone with default knowledge should know this already.\n\nFeel free to propose a better content of this paragraph.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-24T12:45:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-24T12:45:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31311",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Documentation should, of course, reflect the actual workings of a module. At what point did you find it saying that it automatically sets a cache? As the link I provided contained the only paragraph I could find about it.\n\nAnyway, I think the way Zend_Locale handles its cache should be reverted to 1.7.5 and that is to let the programmer decide if he\/she requires a cache or not. Because the current way comes with some rather annoying compatibility issues, which weren't mentioned in a migration chapter. What are your thoughts about the desired behavior?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-24T13:10:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-24T13:10:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31569",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closed issue as the problem is already fixed within Zend_Cache.\nAs alternative the user can also disable the cache within Zend_Locale as described within the manual.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-03T04:09:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-03T04:09:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31686",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I just tried 1.8.2 but the issue still remains. I still gives a \"cache_dir must be a directory\" error.\nI walked through the getTmpDir() method in Zend\/Cache\/Backend.php and the following code, starting at line 181 returns me a so called valid directory.\n\n{code:php}\n        \/\/ Attemp to detect by creating a temporary file\n        $tempFile = tempnam(md5(uniqid(rand(), TRUE)), '');\n        if ($tempFile) {\n        \t$dir = realpath(dirname($tempFile));\n            unlink($tempFile);\n            return $dir;\n        }\n{\/code}\n\nHowever, although PHP is allowed to create a file with tempnam() that doesn't mean that the directory is freely writeable by the user. The directory should be checked with _isGoodTmpDir(). When I do so, the check fails. And eventually I get the exception 'Could not determine temp directory, please specify a cache_dir manually'.\n\nI think the code at least needs to be changed to the following:\n\n{code:php}\n        \/\/ Attemp to detect by creating a temporary file\n        $tempFile = tempnam(md5(uniqid(rand(), TRUE)), '');\n        if ($tempFile) {\n        \t$dir = realpath(dirname($tempFile));\n            unlink($tempFile);\n\t\t\tif($this->_isGoodTmpDir($dir)) {\n\t            return $dir;\n\t\t\t}\n        }\n{\/code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-09T00:19:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-09T00:19:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31688",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, I messed up the formatting. Can't find any edit button to change it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=htbaa",
                        "name": "htbaa",
                        "displayName": "Christiaan Kras",
